Cdata.Personality Traits: She is very apathetic in her social life, but when she is working, she is very kind and considerate. She is only attracted to people drenched in blood but she wont admit that. She is also a bit egotistical despite being self depreciating all the time
Cdata.Motivation for becoming a Hero/Villain: she falsely idolized heroes bc they killed her father for her by accident. She became a medic bc she doesnt enjoy seeing others in pain but she loves being in pain herself, so she plans to potentially serve as a wall for civilians
Cdata.Backstory: Her dad was abusive to his children bc he never wanted them, let alone twins. The mother felt the same so she didnt interfere. Days of starving and being bloodied, she had to learn to love the pain or it would've driven her mad. One day, her father was killed in collateral damage by a hero. At that point she began to praise heroes despite knowing it wasnt intentional. She eventually realized that becoming a hero allowed her to receive all the praise in the world while being constantly affected by pain.

abilities.Faith of Blood:
**__Quirk Template__**

 

Quirk Type: Emitter

Quirk Description: By taking a bath in her blood for 15 minutes or more, you become bonded to her. This allows her to share her pain with you, in exchange for various effects as she learns how to control the blood within you. 

Primary Abilities: Marking people and distributing her own damage to them at a 1-1 ratio

Limitations/Weaknesses: Damage transfer and buffs require her to be in the same category as her marked target,  all future abilities have to be buffs for marked people and not herself. All future abilities are optional to receive by marked targets to prevent them being negative to her marked targets in any way. She cannot drop marked targets below 1 hp with shared damage. Future abilities can be denied if they are not seen as beneficial to her marked targets. Taking a bath while having a desire to no longer be marked removes the mark.

Targets have to bathe in at least 50% of their max hp worth of blood to be marked, otherwise it fails.

abilities.Bloody Mending:
**__Ability Template__**

 

Ability Type: Active

Ability Description: The user can control her blood within peoples body to repair damage. If they are permanently or severely  injured, it takes an 3 hours per meter worth of healing. She can heal more than one  person at a time but it reduces its effectiveness. 

Ability Stage (1st, 2nd, 3rd): 1

Rolls/Effect(s): quirk/5 + vitality/4 divided amongst all targets equally.

Ability Drawback: takes her action so she can't fight. They have to be marked by bathing in her blood for a minimum of 15 minutes.

Character #: 1

Cdata.Personality Traits: Detached from life. She has strong empathy, so if she doesn't detach herself, everything she sees will kill her
Cdata.Motivation for becoming a Hero/Villain: She wants to protect the spirits and be a bridge between the two. A lot of ayakashi have rough lives.
Cdata.Backstory: She was born on a shrine in a small town. Her mother was a shrine maiden with unrivaled beauty, so everyone adored her, that is, until her child out with a dark elfs appearance. In kindergarten, she awakened her quirk that laid dormant. She could now see creatures that were there. Spirits, ayakashi, and even kami would speak to her. One night, a kami who she didnt know took control of her body, and slaughtered everyone in the shrine. She had no control over her actions and wasnt even aware of what happened till after. She was a scared child, that is, until an old man approached her shortly after, it was her grandfather, apparently he could see the creatures too. His quirk allowed him to travel between the far shore and near shore, living in the world of ayakashi. Thus, she grew up in a mansion ruled by the oni. She became close with a red oni who told her a blue ogre possessed her back then. Even tho they couldnt be in a contract, they are close friends. Without her knowledge, her grandfather set up a marriage between her childhood friend and her. But before she could pry answers from him, he passed away. Afterwards, the oni ruler insisted that she return to the human world because her grandfather could no longer traverse her world. Thus, she was sent back, with only her fiancee who promised to protect her against ayakashi. No one knows she was the one who destroyed that shrine... But she still cant come out of hiding, she needs to make the world a place for ayakashi as much as the far shore. And protect humans from ayakashi.

abilities.Total Communion:
**__Quirk Template__**

 

Quirk Type: Emitter

Quirk Description: The user has modified senses to be able to notice kami, yokai, onis, and the spirits within living things (and previously living). She can talk to them but they dont care for the human world, if they were once human, they cant share their story without a contract, so unless they are given orders via a contract, they dont care enough to discover useful information. All spirits are incorporeal to anyone but her

In order to form a contract, she has to offer them something they deem worthy of giving up their free will for. This is not an easy task, thus its incredibly difficult trial and error to discover what each type of spirit will accept. Even with a contract, her quirk isnt strong enough to connect with humanoid spirits (level 10)

All spirits have benefits to having under a contract, the weaker they are, the weaker their effect, but the easier they are to contract. All effects have to be listed in the ability allowing her to contract to that species. 

Primary Abilities: forming contracts with hearing/seeing spirits. 

Limitations/Weaknesses: only humanoid spirits can go anywhere they want, other spirits require a source nearby, for example, water spirits need a large amount of water. She herself is a source for all contracted spirits, but then they cant leave her side. They are useless without a contract. Max 2 contracts + 1 per level gained. She cant hear anything without a spirit.

Each spirit type will have a personality, failure to properly play that personality may result in deletion of that ability. Future contracts can buff her but unless explicitly stated otherwise, spirits cant attack.

abilities.Beast Feast (Carnophage):
**__Quirk Template__**

 

Quirk Type: Transformation

Quirk Description:

This Quirk allows the user to transform into various creatures by consuming biological material. Initially, it only works on animals, but upon awakening, it extends to humans with Quirks. By ingesting even a small sample (such as a bite), the user undergoes a full-body transformation into a monstrous version of the consumed entity. (Once fully awakened) If they consume multiple sources, their form may take on hybrid characteristics.

Consuming animal flesh triggers a full-body transformation into a mutated version of that creature (e.g., eating beef turns them into a minotaur-like being).

Biting a human with a Quirk allows them to take on an adapted version of that power in their transformation (e.g., biting Endeavour results in a fire-elemental form).

(Once Fully Awakened): If multiple sources are consumed, the transformation becomes a fusion of traits (e.g., a bat-wolf hybrid if both are eaten).

If taken from a non-willing party, instead of her keeping it permanently, the user must roll a d10 to determine how long it will last; with a 10 being a perma-keep and a 1 meaning it doesn't register inside her body (all individual values will be given a list of time that will be inserted here soon).

Primary Abilities:

Apex Predator: While transformed, the users physicality scales with the creatures natural abilities. This ability gives her a passive buff to the form's most appropriate stat in base (will just be whatever the mutant's is if she bites one of them).


Limitations/Weaknesses:

- Limited Duration: Transformations last for a Medium Transformation Length (15 turns)

- Quirk Decay: The user cannot permanently retain any Quirk-based transformations from non-consenters (unless she rolls a 10 for a human); they revert back after the effect wears off (time varies for humans based on her initial bite roll).

- Physical Strain: Rapid shifting between forms causes fatigue, and overuse can lead to severe exhaustion or even temporary immobilization. (Switching forms costs a turn)

- Selective Digestion: Only fresh biological material triggers transformationsprocessed or cooked foods do not work.

- Biting a Quirkless Individual: Results in no transformation, wasting the attempt.

Cdata.Personality Traits: Masaki is a very quiet and hard working individual. on the surface he seems like a very lazy and apathetic person. He is often noticed by his tired and rugged attitude constantly seen with a unhealthy amount of cigarettes or coffee. He has a habit of pushing himself further than he should without even realizing that he is doing it. This can come into play with a sort of hyper fixation effect.
Cdata.Motivation for becoming a Hero/Villain: He pursues the job as a hero to use the money to fund into his shops welfare as well as promoting it to the general public. He also deeply wishes to prevent what happened to his father to happen to others.
Cdata.Backstory: He was born to a hero and a small business owner. His mother was a strong and proud hero capable of storing and releasing powerful amounts of energy. His father was a simple and humble spider like mutant who used his silk to create beautiful items such as clothing, art, materials and even misc items like baskets or blankets. They lived comfortably in that shop. His father deeply loved his work and showed that appreciation to his son who was born blind. His mother while cared for and was deeply protective of their son was usually gone and did not know how to properly interact with their sons troubles.

Cdata.Personality Traits: Alexander is a rather calm individual. He practices self-control in dire need and holds his tongue whenever he deems it necessary. He isn't one to start problems nor indulge in selfish and self-centered concepts like pride and hate. There's nothing that really affects him on a scale large enough to get a rise out of him. Alexander gets this passive personality because of his father's business-like relationship with himself. His father sees Alexander as his heir, and solely his heir. Therefore the boy's training throughout his childhood was harsh and conditioned, a perfect balance between challenge and fun. This made for a business-like approach to all scenarios. Despite this, Alexander seems carefree and naturally bored. He has a resting point of serenity and is usually lost in incoherent thoughts too fast for his brain to process all at a time. He's dignified but careless.
Cdata.Backstory: Alexander Von-Der-Leyen was born in Munich, Germany to a royal blooded family. Alexander has since forth received preparations for his inevitable inheritance of the family business, and in turn the potential of his family name. Training starting as soon as his powers were inherited, and he was given top notch and state of the art regimens. Alexander was given many years in Germany, in which he was eventually transferred to Japan in order to attend a top notch school for the gifted youth. He eventually left for more training, but has come back in the recent year to attend a promising college built for hero courses. Alexander's studies has now went abroad to several countries, however Japan has been his favorite, and his choice to study in.

Cdata.Backstory: Numb. That was the only feeling Mahi had ever felt. Life didnt have any buzz or edge. The constant itchy feeling tingled through his body but nothing could quite satiate the need. That was until one fateful evening. Walking home, a mugger attempted to rob Mahi and, in the moment, something inside him began to flair up, a new feeling. Adrenaline was coursing through his veins for the first time and it shot him to life. A giant smirk overtook his face as he lunged at the attacker, knocking him into the ground before beating him to death, laughing maniacally with each crunch of breaking bone. It was only after he had stopped to breathe that he noticed the knife buried in his stomach. He pulled it out and calmly made his way to find medical attention, still smiling wide. Mahi had finally found something that made him feel alive, taking the life of someone else.
